Homework
Instructions for locating homework results using the GitHub resource https://github.com/:


1. Create an identifiable account or use an existing identifiable account, i.e. your user name = your real name

2. Make it public

3. Create a repository for the course assignment,

for example: yourusername/DataAnalysis_2026



4. Create a separate folder for each module,

for example: Data Manipulation and Cleaning

The contents of each folder:

a. Readme file - description (assignment, data description, R version, procedures used, etc.)

b. Source file with data

c. File(s) with code

d. File(s) with output data: analysis results/graphs
